# Slint UI Rules

- All declarative layout lives in `.slint` files under `ui_application/ui/`.
- Business logic and state mutations live in `.rs` files; never embed logic in Slint markup.
- Import standard widgets: `import { Button, LineEdit, VerticalBox } from "std-widgets.slint";`
- UI crate may depend on `core_domain` traits/types but must not import `infrastructure/` directly.
- Use callbacks (`callback name(type);`) to bridge UI events to Rust handlers.
- Bind state with properties (`in-out property <string> name`) and two-way binding (`<=>`).
